# Inventory / Marketplace MVP

Internal inventory is the **source of truth**, integrated with marketplaces (Shopee/Tokopedia
now). **Adapter-first with STUBS** so the whole pipeline runs without real provider APIs.
Per-user scoped (internal-first, multi-tenant-ready). Roadmap + locked decisions:
`docs/roadmap/inventory-mvp.md`.

## Modules & domains
- **catalog** — Product / ProductVariant (master). Server service owns Prisma (no repository).
  A product has **0..N** variants (create-without-variant is allowed; add them later from the detail
  page). The **variant is the SKU/stock leaf** (`@@unique([userId, sku])`); **`variantGroup String?`**
  is an optional grouping **label** above it — a variant is EITHER a **standalone SKU** OR a **named
  group of subvariant SKUs** (siblings share one `variantGroup`, e.g. group "iPhone 16" → "Hitam"/
  "Putih"). Grouping is **display-only**: stock/ledger/orders/sales/PO/marketplace all stay at the leaf
  — there is NO deeper stock-bearing level. Builders share `components/variant-blocks-field.tsx`
  (`VariantBlocksField` via `useFormContext`) in the create + add-variant + add-subvariant dialogs;
  `utils/variants.ts` owns `buildVariantBlocks` (group/standalone layout), `suggestVariantSku`
  (vowel-strip compaction, wand button), `formatVariantLabel` ("group · name"). Variant carries
  `cost`/`weight`, `lowStockThreshold`/`alertEnabled`, reorder planning `leadTimeDays?`/`minOrderQty?`
  (0 in the UI = unset → null), and a **per-variant photo** `imageKey?`/`imageUrl?` (separate PUBLIC R2
  bucket — see Gotchas). Variants are editable: `PATCH /products/:id/variants/:variantId` →
  `updateVariant` (create/add-variant forms stay short; advanced planning is set later via Edit).
  Bulk add: `POST /products/:id/variants` `{ variants:[] }` → `addVariants` (all leaves in one tx).
  Stock changes go through the inventory service, NEVER by writing inventory tables from catalog.
  **Delete** (soft, `deletedAt`) of a product / variant / whole group is **guarded by a cross-module
  preflight** `getDeletionBlockers` (`GET /products/:id/deletion-blockers?variantIds=`): **BLOCKED** when
  any active variant is marketplace-mapped, has `reserved>0` or `incoming>0`, or has an open (PENDING)
  return; **WARNS** (still allowed) on available on-hand + damaged stock; pending unpaid orders ignored.
  Soft-delete mangles the SKU (`archivedSku` → `<sku>::deleted::<id>`) so it **frees for reuse** (the
  unique index spans archived rows; safe — Sale/Order items snapshot sku). No restore UI yet.
  **QR labels**: `/dashboard/labels` label studio — `listLabelVariants` (paginated; already-printed
  sort last via `labelPrintedAt nulls-first`), prints an A4 grid encoding `barcode ?? sku`.
  `ProductVariant.labelPrintedAt` + `markLabelsPrinted` (`POST /products/variants/printed`) stamp the
  last print; shown in the picker + the shared `QrCodeDialog` (product-detail inline `QrImage`,
  inventory ⋯ action). Endpoints: `GET /products/variants?q=&page=&pageSize=` (label list),
  `POST /products/variants/printed`.
- **inventory** — `Inventory` (fast-read cache: available/reserved/damaged/incoming) +
  **`StockLedger` (append-only = the real source of truth, available-centric)**. Every mutation =
  1 ledger row + 1 Inventory update in ONE tx. `adjustStock` (manual, never negative). Inbound-order
  stock **lifecycle trio** (all `(tx,…)`, available MAY go negative): `applyOrderReserveTx`
  (available−, reserved+; `ORDER_RESERVE`), `applyOrderShipTx` (reserved− only, available unchanged;
  `ORDER_SHIP` delta 0), `applyOrderReleaseTx` (available+, reserved−; `ORDER_RELEASE`). Reserved
  decrements clamp at 0 (+warn) for orders reserved before the lifecycle existed; on-hand = available
  + reserved. Other modules' SoT writes also funnel through here: `applyReturnRestockTx`/
  `applyReturnDamagedTx` (returns), `applyOfflineSaleTx` (POS — available−, `SALE`/`POS`),
  `adjustIncomingTx`/`applyPurchaseReceiveTx` (purchasing — the `incomingStock` bucket). Surfaces: `getDashboard` (KPIs incl. `totalReservedUnits`); `listStockOverview` (now also the
  last movement before→after + `lastAdjustedAt`, via a nested `take:1` ledger include); **reorder
  report** (`inventory-reorder.service` — recency-weighted/EWMA velocity → days-of-cover → suggested
  qty, honours per-variant lead time/MOQ; bucketed ledger sums per sub-window); **stock activity
  log** (`inventory-activity.service` — filter reason/source/direction/date + paginate + CSV export).
  Demand reasons for velocity are centralised in `SALES_LEDGER_REASONS` (ORDER_RESERVE + ORDER_RELEASE
  + RETURN + SALE, NOT delta-0 ORDER_SHIP — avoids double-count; nets returns + counts offline POS
  sales). Pure `utils/stock-math.ts` + `utils/reorder-math.ts` are unit-tested.
- **marketplace** — connections (`MarketplaceConnection`; now also `lastOrdersPulledAt`) +
  `MarketplaceProduct` (listing snapshot) + `MarketplaceProductMapping` (listing↔variant). Mapping
  is **1:1 on the listing** (`marketplaceProductId @unique`) but ONE variant MAY map to many
  listings — cross-channel sync is by design, do NOT force 1:1. Import via STUB adapter; auto-map by
  NORMALIZED sku (`utils/sku-match.ts`, NOT edit-distance — `…-M` ≠ `…-L`); non-exact →
  `NEEDS_REVIEW` + sync stays off (per-listing sync is a **Switch**, disabled while NEEDS_REVIEW).
  `mapByExternalRef` upserts a listing (creating its snapshot if never imported) + its mapping.
- **orders** — **multi-store pull** `pullFromConnections(connectionIds?)` (default every active
  store; STUB adapter) → resolve items via mapping → advance the per-order **stock lifecycle** (each
  stage once, idempotent via `Order.inventoryAppliedAt`/`inventoryShippedAt`/`inventoryRevertedAt`):
  RESERVE on PAID, SHIP on SHIPPED/COMPLETED (consumes the reservation; an order first seen already
  shipped reserves then ships), RELEASE on CANCELLED-before-ship. CANCELLED-**after**-ship is a return,
  NOT a release (goods already left → no credit): it auto-opens a return via the returns service
  (best-effort). Only available changes (reserve/release) propagate to OTHER channels — excluding the
  source channel (`excludeConnectionId`); ship does not. Per-store **30s cooldown** keyed on
  `lastOrdersPulledAt` (skipped, not errored = anti-abuse). `resolveOrderItem` maps an unmapped item
  from the order page (via `mapByExternalRef`) then reserves stock for just the newly-resolved items of
  a PAID order (idempotent). Endpoints: `POST /api/v1/orders/pull`, `/orders/:id/resolve-item`. Pull
  lives on the **Orders** page (removed from marketplace detail).
- **fulfillment (Phase 5)** — orders ↔ packing videos are joined by the shared **`noResi`**
  (no FK; matched **case-insensitively** — the resi input is NOT force-uppercased, the scanner is).
  `Order.fulfilledAt` is stamped best-effort when a packing video completes (the recordings complete
  route calls `markFulfilledByResi` — never fails the save). `findByResi` resolves the order for a resi
  (the station **pack view** shows its items via `useOrderByResiQuery`); recordings `findByResi` lists
  completed videos for a resi (order/return **evidence**, via `useRecordingsByResiQuery`). Links work
  **both ways**: order/return → packing video, and the recording detail modal + pack view → order.
  Services stay decoupled — composition is at the route/page/hook layer. Endpoints:
  `GET /api/v1/orders/by-resi`, `GET /api/v1/recordings/by-resi`.
- **returns** — RMA flow (`Return` + `ReturnItem`). A return opens (PENDING) for an order whose goods
  shipped — auto on a detected post-ship cancellation, or manually from the order page — then is
  processed once goods arrive: each line routed to **RESTOCK** (`applyReturnRestockTx`, available+) or
  **DAMAGED** (`applyReturnDamagedTx`, damagedStock+, delta-0 ledger), via the inventory service in one
  tx; restocks propagate to all channels. Ledger reason `RETURN`; restock nets out reorder velocity
  (`SALES_LEDGER_REASONS`). Idempotent (one return per order). Return detail links the packing video by
  `noResi` (dispute evidence). Endpoints: `GET/POST /api/v1/returns`, `/returns/:id`,
  `/returns/:id/process`, `/returns/:id/reject`.
- **sales (offline / POS)** — `Sale` + `SaleItem` (snapshot sku/name/unitPrice), `SalePaymentMethod`
  (CASH/QRIS/TRANSFER), `SaleStatus` (COMPLETED/VOID), code `S00001` per-user. A counter sale
  **decrements the SoT immediately**: one tx creates the sale + lines and calls `applyOfflineSaleTx`
  per line (`available−`, ledger `SALE` / source `POS` / ref = saleId, `note: 'Offline sale'`). Oversell
  is **allowed** (goods are in hand → available MAY go negative). After commit, propagate each sold
  variant's new available to **all** sync-ready channels (selling in-store can't oversell online). The
  POS picker reads ProductVariant read-only (`searchSellableVariants`, active only, by sku/name + price +
  available). `SALE` joins `SALES_LEDGER_REASONS`, so offline sales feed reorder velocity. **Scan-to-cart**
  (`usePosScanner`, `scanner-pairing` purpose **POS**): a paired phone scans a product label →
  `resolveSellableVariant` (barcode-then-sku, case-insensitive) → cart line, repeat scan bumps qty, with a
  browser beep. Endpoints: `GET/POST /api/v1/sales`, `/sales/:id`, `/sales/variants?q=`,
  `/sales/variants/resolve?code=`.
- **purchasing (restock / POs)** — `PurchaseOrder` + `PurchaseOrderItem` (snapshot sku/name + `quantity`/
  `receivedQuantity`/`unitCost`), `PurchaseOrderStatus` ORDERED→PARTIALLY_RECEIVED→RECEIVED/CANCELLED,
  code `PO00001` per-user. **Lights up the `incomingStock` bucket** (the last empty one). Two inventory
  tx-methods (no over-credit): `adjustIncomingTx(tx,{variantId,delta})` — `incomingStock += delta`
  clamped at 0, **NO ledger row** (forecast bucket, available unchanged); `applyPurchaseReceiveTx` —
  `incoming−` (clamped) + `available+`, ledger `RESTOCK` / source `PURCHASE` / ref = PO id. Lifecycle:
  **create** (already ORDERED) → `adjustIncomingTx(+qty)` per line + `totalCost`; **receive** (only
  ORDERED/PARTIALLY_RECEIVED, per-line qty clamped to outstanding) → `receivedQuantity +=` +
  `applyPurchaseReceiveTx`, recompute status (all received → RECEIVED + `receivedAt`, else
  PARTIALLY_RECEIVED), propagate received variants to **all** channels; **cancel** (not-yet-RECEIVED) →
  `adjustIncomingTx(−outstanding)` per line, status CANCELLED (already-received units stay in available).
  `supplierName` is **free text** (no Supplier entity yet); variant `cost` stays manual. `searchVariants`
  reads ProductVariant read-only (cost + available + incoming), now **paginated** (`?q=&page=&pageSize=`).
  The reorder report's **"Create PO"** prefills `/dashboard/purchasing/new` from URGENT/SOON suggestions.
  **Scan-to-order** (`usePurchaseScanner`, `scanner-pairing` purpose **PURCHASING**): a paired phone scans
  a product label → `resolvePurchasableVariant` → PO line, repeat scan bumps qty, browser beep. Endpoints:
  `GET/POST /api/v1/purchase-orders`, `/purchase-orders/:id`, `/:id/receive`, `/:id/cancel`,
  `/purchase-orders/variants?q=&page=&pageSize=`, `/purchase-orders/variants/resolve?code=`.

## Outbound sync engine (worker-side) — `packages/queue/src/marketplace-sync/`
SoT change → `enqueuePropagateInventoryStock` (web, best-effort, only if `syncEnabled` mappings
exist) → `propagate-inventory-stock` job (fan-out, idempotent per ledger event) →
`sync-marketplace-stock` job → `executeStockSync` (per-provider rate-limit, push LATEST
available via the provider adapter; `Dev` stub simulates success, `Unwired` stub rejects) →
marks `MarketplaceSyncJob` + mapping `lastSyncStatus` + listing snapshot. Retryable failures
throw so BullMQ retries.

## Cross-module composition (respect boundary §3)
- catalog→inventory ONLY via the inventory service (no cross-table writes). orders→inventory via
  the lifecycle trio (`applyOrderReserveTx`/`ShipTx`/`ReleaseTx`); orders→returns via its service
  (auto-open). returns→inventory via `applyReturnRestockTx`/`DamagedTx` and reads Order/OrderItem
  read-only. sales→inventory via `applyOfflineSaleTx`; purchasing→inventory via `adjustIncomingTx`/
  `applyPurchaseReceiveTx` — both read ProductVariant read-only for their pickers and propagate to
  ALL channels after commit (a counter sale or restock moves sellable everywhere). A module may import
  another module's HOOKS/types but NOT its components — cross-module UI composition lives at the APP
  layer (e.g. `app/(dashboard)/dashboard/products/[id]/product-detail-view.tsx` wires catalog
  `ProductDetail` + inventory `AdjustStockDialog`; the reorder report's "Create PO" links into
  purchasing). The variant picker reuses inventory `useStockOverviewQuery`.

## Gotchas (learned the hard way)
- **Two R2 buckets, PER-BUCKET public URLs.** Recordings bucket is **PRIVATE** (playback via presigned
  GET); variant images live in a **separate PUBLIC** bucket. Env: `R2_RECORDINGS_BUCKET_NAME` +
  `R2_PUBLIC_URL` (recordings) · `R2_PRODUCTS_BUCKET_NAME` + `R2_PRODUCTS_PUBLIC_URL` (products). Each
  bucket has its **own** public base; the object URL is `<base>/<key>` with **NO bucket name in the
  path** — r2.dev binds one domain per bucket and serves at the root. Do NOT do `${base}/${bucket}/${key}`
  (it returns 400 → `ERR_BLOCKED_BY_ORB`, image won't render — a reverted dead end). Keys: recordings
  `{userId}/{y}/{m}/file`, products `{userId}/{file}` (`generateProductImageKey`); `isUserStorageKey` =
  `startsWith('{userId}/')`. Image upload is `POST /uploads/presign-image` (client compresses to WebP
  ≤1600px via `utils/compress-image.ts`) → PUT to R2 → `PATCH /products/:id/variants/:variantId/image`
  (stores key + server-computed public URL). `apply-r2-cors` covers both buckets (PUT for upload only;
  `<img>` GET needs no CORS). `imageUrl` is computed at upload time, so changing the URL scheme means
  old rows keep stale URLs → re-upload.
- **BullMQ custom jobId CANNOT contain `:`** → job-id builders use `-` (DB idempotency keys keep `:`).
- A real provider adapter needs the **DECRYPTED token** → lift marketplace token-crypto into a
  shared `@olshop/*` package (the engine passes the encrypted token; stubs ignore it).
- A running dev server (`tsx watch server.ts`) holds the Prisma query-engine DLL on Windows →
  `prisma generate` fails `EPERM`. Stop it before generate/migrate; restart after. BUT an
  index-only / no-client-change migration can run with `prisma migrate dev --skip-generate`
  WITHOUT stopping the dev server (only `generate` overwrites the locked DLL).
- `next build` intermittently fails `Failed to collect page data for /<page>` while node procs
  run (a `.next` file-lock flake) — just re-run; not a code error.
- `server-only` services can't be imported into a worker-context `tsx` script without
  `node --conditions=react-server` + the web tsconfig.
- Typed routes: after adding a new `app/**/page.tsx`, `pnpm typecheck` (`tsc`) fails on `Route`
  literals until `next build` regenerates `.next/types`. Build first, then typecheck.

## QR-scan (POS phase 2) — ✅ shipped
**Phase A — QR labels**: `/dashboard/labels` (catalog) + `ProductVariant.labelPrintedAt` (last-print
tracking) + shared `QrImage`/`QrCodeDialog` on the product-detail & inventory tables (above). **Phase B —
scan-to-cart/order**: POS (`usePosScanner`, purpose POS) and New PO (`usePurchaseScanner`, purpose
PURCHASING) add a line by scanning a product label (repeat = +qty), reusing **`scanner-pairing`** — see
`30-scanner-pairing.mdc` for the purpose split, verbatim `scannedCodeSchema`, QR+1D reader, and
browser-only sound. Realtime needs the socket host (`server.ts`, gated off on Vercel) → dev/VPS only.

## Paginated tables (shared)
Inventory overview, the label picker, and the New-PO product picker use `usePagination` +
`TablePagination` (rows-per-page 10/20/50/100, resets to page 1). The label + PO pickers are
**server-paginated** (service returns `PaginatedResult`, route forwards `page`/`pageSize`); inventory
paginates client-side over its capped overview. See `50-ui-design-system.mdc`.

## Deferred (raise as separate suggestions)
ProviderHealth + reconciliation/drift; bundles/kits; multi-warehouse; per-order re-pull (pull is
store-level only); PENDING-order reservation (needs expiry/auto-release); within returns: per-line
split (part restock + part damaged), partial-quantity returns, refund/money tracking, marketplace
return-API sync; a `StockLedger (userId, createdAt)` index for the activity feed at scale (the
`(userId, reason, createdAt)` index serves reorder); **purchasing**: Supplier entity (contacts,
per-supplier lead time), auto **cost update** on receive (moving-average → profit reporting), PO
edit/DRAFT, supplier invoice (faktur) printing, landed cost; **POS**: VOID/refund a sale, printable
receipt/nota, per-sale discount/tax; reorder velocity is a simple EWMA (could add seasonality); real
provider adapters need the decrypted token → lift token-crypto to `@olshop/*`; queue package has no
vitest (engine is gate-checked only).

